      "side": 1,
      "message": "If you covert this to only use a texture view then you can no longer copy it right? In the proxy level it will not be flagged as framebuffer only (since it comes form a backend texture) so it make think it can attempt a copy to do some operation. But then that is going to fail down here when try to actually execute the GPU command.\n\nThis is why I was suggesting the GrDawnRenderTarget should hold a texture and/or a textureview.  The pure wrap GrBackendRenderTarget will creating a framebuffer only GrDawnRT that only has a view, but this case will be able to create one that does a wrap a texture.",
